ce:section.ce:para:
The impacts of NH2-GOQDs loading on the water flux (Jv
                        ) and the reverse salt flux (Js
                        ) of each membrane were explored at FO mode and PRO mode using DI water as the feed solution and 0.5 M NaCl solution as the draw solution. The results are shown in Fig. 8
                        . Overall, except for the TFN-5 membrane, the water flux of all the NH2-GOQDs-incorporated TFN membranes was higher than the TFC membrane. The primary reason was that the hydrophilicity of PA layer was improved due to abundant hydrophilic functional groups on NH2-GOQDs which was beneficial to the dissolution of water molecules on the membrane surface [54], so as to improve the permeability of water. In addition, in the process of IP reaction, NH2-GOQDs blocked the diffusion of MPD into the organic phase and affected the formation of ridge structure in the PA layer. The small-scale ridge structure shortened the water transmission distance and reduced the mass transfer resistance of water, thus improving water flux. In addition, ultra-small NH2-GOQDs nanoparticles could provide many nanochannels between the NH2-GOQDs and the PA layer [55], resulting in the increase of water flux. Interestingly, the change of water flux was not regular. This was because the effective surface area of PA layer decreased with the decline of membrane surface roughness, which was unfavorable for the increase of water flux. The transition of water flux was a common result induced by these three factors including hydrophilicity, structure and roughness. In spite of this, TFN-2 and TFN-3 membrane showed the water flux of 26.57 and 25.03 LMH, which was still about 21% higher than that of traditional TFC membrane under PRO mode.
